What NICE guidelines for CVD prevention would be suitable for John, given his profile - a 70-year-old Chinese man, with a BMI of 30, blood pressure of 114/61 mmHg, total cholesterol of 6.7 mmol/L, HDL cholesterol of 1.0 mmol/L, current smoker, doesn't have diabetes, and a family history of CVD? \\ \end{tabular}
\begin{tabular}{p{142.3pt} p{142.3pt}} \hline \hline
**Answer** & The NICE guidelines recommend a stepped approach to CVD prevention, with increasing intensity of interventions based on the individual's risk. John's CVD risk is estimated to be 17\% over 10 years, which is above the threshold for moderate intensity interventions. He should be offered lifestyle advice, including weight loss and smoking cessation. He should also be offered a statin for primary prevention, given his high total cholesterol and low HDL cholesterol. \\ \hline \hline \end{tabular}
